column7: Limiting a license to a time window
column8: As a Sage account manager I can set time windows on features that I include in a license so that Sage can sell features in subscription mode.

As a Sage account manager I can deliver licenses that limit the number or valid records in specific tables so that Sage can charge according to the volume of data stored in the application.
As a Sage account manager I can collect usage counters on specific tables so that Sage can charge according to the number of transactions (typically number of sales orders, number of pay slips, etc.)
As a syracuse administrator I can monitor the usage counters defined by my license so that I can anticipate how much I will be charged by Sage.
As a Sage account manager I can create signed license files so that the application rejects the license if it has been tampered by a customer or partner.

As a Sage product manager I can configure the list of functions that the license will unlock in a given badge so that Sage can tune its license policy.
As a ERP User I can view the license of my software so that I can find out what has been purchased by my company.
As a syracuse administrator I can activate a license that I have received from Sage so that my users can use the software according to the license that we purchased.
As a Sage account manager I can deliver demo licenses so that Sage pre-sales and partners can demo the product.
